1.title: Hereford and Gloucester
1.plot: Phil heads for the two cathedral cities. He helps exes Nick and Carolyn in Gloucester, and Lorna and Stuart, who are cramped in Hereford.

2.title: Mersey
2.plot: Phil's on a mission on the Mersey, trying to shift two homes suffering from dodgy décor and problem pooches.

3.title: Bath
3.plot: Phil Spencer is in Bath, helping a couple who've had their place on the market for an incredible five years. He also meets Sam and Maria, whose back garden looks like a builder's yard.

4.plot:

5.title: The North
5.plot: Phil seeks buyers for two struggling semis in the north of England. Can he help former cabbie Allan in Gosforth and Dawn and Daz in Ripponden, Yorkshire, with their shabby interiors?

6.title: Leicestershire
6.plot: In Market Harborough, Phil meets John and Jane, whose house has been on the market for a year. And in the village of Countesthorpe, Elaine is struggling to sell the family home.

1.title: Leeds
1.plot: Phil meets the Fozards, who have outgrown their three-bed semi. But after eight months on the market and 18 viewings, they've had no offers. The family are worn out. Unfortunately, so is the house.

2.title: Brighton
2.plot: Phil travels to the south coast to help mum Martina and nan Peggy sell both their houses and move in together.

3.title: Radcliffe
3.plot: Phil Spencer helps the owners of a two-bed terrace in Stoneclough near Bolton that is crammed with enough knick-knacks and decorative touches to fill an auction house but just won't sell.

4.title: Balham
4.plot: Phil Spencer gives property advice to two friends who have been struggling for 15 months to sell their three-bedroom flat in south-west London but have had no luck even after 42 viewings.

5.title: Altrincham
5.plot: Phil Spencer advises on how to spruce up and sell a three-bedroom detached cottage on the outskirts of Manchester that has been on the market for a staggering four years with no offers.

6.title: Dorking
6.plot: Phil's latest secret mission takes him to Dorking, where he finds a period property that's charming on the outside and a little bit alarming on the inside.

7.title: Riccall
7.plot: In the north Yorkshire village of Riccall, Phil Spencer meets Lawrence and Catherine Bendelow, who are struggling to sell a house they've been renting out to tenants for four years.

8.title: Harrogate
8.plot: In Harrogate Phil meets Andrew and Jenna, whose three-bed in the exclusive Duchy area should have flown off the shelf. But on closer inspection he finds some serious problems lurking.

9.title: Milford
9.plot: Phil visits Milford, a small but perfectly formed village not far from Godalming, Surrey, where Nick Walsh's three-bed house leaves him flabbergasted.

10.title: Wakefield
10.plot: Property expert Phil Spencer visits Wakefield to help the Murphy family sell their higgledy-piggledy, end-of-terrace home in a hurry so they can start a new life in Perth, Australia.

11.title: Llanharan
11.plot: It's an undercover operation of the Welsh-valley variety for Agent Spencer as he finds himself in Llanharan, Pontyclun, with a house for sale that's in need of a re-vamp.

12.title: Pinner
12.plot: Today Phil's Secret Agent mission takes him to the affluent area of Pinner in Harrow and the five-bed family home of Vaseem, Ayeesha and their two children.

13.title: Llandaff
13.plot: Phil visits the Welsh capital of Cardiff and a 1940s bachelor pad that's a bacteria fest of unclean surfaces, grimy floors and manky carpets.

14.title: Watford
14.plot: Phil's latest secret assignment takes him to Watford and the four-bed detached house of John and Mirasol Lockwood, and Emma Green and Steve Wright and their dog Bruno.

15.title: New Malden
15.plot: It's a secret mission to challenge the very best of them as Phil heads to New Malden in Surrey, and a semi-detached family home which has the busy A3 in the front garden.

16.title: Bristol
16.plot: Phil Spencer is in Ashton, Bristol helping David Wood sell his three bedroom house.

17.title: Croydon
17.plot: Phil Spencer helps Kerry and Rowan sell their three bedroom family home in south London.

18.title: Bristol
18.plot: Phil Spencer visits Hallam, near Bristol, to help Becky and Mike sell their three bedroom terrace house, which has had only five viewings in five months on the market.

19.title: Swansea
19.plot: Phil visits a home near Swansea in south west Wales which owners, John and Layla Morrissey and their family, have outgrown.

20.title: Orpington
20.plot: Phil is in the fourth week of his mission to get Britain moving again, travelling in and around England and Wales to help shift several properties stuck in the property quagmire.

1.title: Manchester
1.plot: Phil is in desirable Didsbury, where Marty and Ceris are selling their four bed semi-detached. Meanwhile on the other side of the city, Kristian and Lori's semi is only half finished.

2.title: Leeds
2.plot: Phil travels to Leeds on a secret mission to get offers on houses that haven't been selling. Tim's three-bed semi should have been snapped up, while Caroline's bungalow needs an update.

3.title: Kent
3.plot: Phil's mission is in commuter-belt Kent, where two properties get some secret agent assistance after being on the market almost two years between them.

4.title: Shropshire and Worcestershire
4.plot: Phil escapes the rat race and heads for the country, to earth mother Oriole's five-bedroom home in the sleepy Shropshire hills, and Annette's cottage in Worcestershire.

5.title: Birmingham
5.plot: Phil is in Birmingham trying to sell two tricky terraces on the same street. While Vicky and Phil try to clear the kiddie clutter, Phil and Martha-Ann take on their distasteful decor.

6.title: Glasgow
6.plot: Phil goes undercover in Scotland, trying to get offers on two houses not far from Glasgow's busy city centre, in Giffnock and Uddingston.

7.title: Cheshire and Lancashire
7.plot: Phil Spencer visits a family in Northwich and a couple in Bromley Cross, Bolton.

8.title: Edinburgh and Largs
8.plot: Phil visits a three bed home in one of Edinburgh's poshest post codes, and a bungalow on the north Ayrshire coast, both of which are struggling to find a buyer.

9.title: Warrington
9.plot: Phil is in Warrington, helping Pauline and Alan Jacks and Colin Brunold find house buyers in a town that is a bit of a dark horse in terms of property values.

10.title: East Midlands
10.plot: In Stamford in the East Midlands, Phil Spencer works with Mark and Tina Harrison, whose three bed home is hardly rocking the younger market's world.

11.title: Shoreham and Worthing
11.plot: Phil meets Ben and Kate in their Grade II listed cottage in Shoreham-by-Sea and super-busy single mum Zoe in Worthing.

12.title: Reigate and Haslemere
12.plot: Phil visits a property in Reigate, Surrey that looks like a sauna. And in Haslemere he assists an estate agent who can't sell her home.

13.title: The Wirral and West Yorkshire
13.plot: Phil goes undercover on the Wirral, to rescue Dave and Gemma's five bed semi from Dave's 'man cave'. And in Marsden in West Yorkshire helps Malcolm and Muriel.

14.title: Ashurst Wood and Weybridge
14.plot: Phil helps a retired couple in Ashurst Wood to make their cluttered 1950s house more appealing, and a Weybridge brother and sister get advice on bringing their 60s home back to the future.

15.title: West Yorkshire
15.plot: Phil visits West Yorkshire, where Jean desperately needs help to shift her home, and retired teacher Mary's country cottage has lost its charm.

16.title: Harrogate and Huddersfield
16.plot: A four bed semi in Harrogate in need of some upkeep, and a cottage in Huddersfield with some decidedly dodgy and dated decor, are the latest hard-to-sell homes for Phil to tackle.

17.title: Billericay and Southend-on-Sea
17.plot: In Billericay, in Essex, Julie is desperate to sell their out-of-control house. And in Southend, Phil meets serial mover June, whose home is overbearingly pink.

1.title: Billericay, Essex
1.plot: Phil helps an Essex mum and her four sons to get their ramshackle home into a condition which will attract buyers' offers at an open viewing in just two weeks.

2.title: East Midlands
2.plot: Phil takes on a two bed terrace in one of the toughest property markets in the UK as he heads to Syston in the East Midlands.

3.title: Radcliffe, Manchester
3.plot: In Radcliffe, Greater Manchester, Phil meets the Young family to cast his eye over their property and try to get them a buyer.

4.title: Bishop's Stortford
4.plot: Phil Spencer is in the market town of Bishop's Stortford taking on a house that's been on the market for six months with hardly a sniff of a buyer.

5.title: Leicestershire
5.plot: Phil advises the owners of an unloved home in Fleckney, Leicestershire, on how to get their house in order for an open viewing in just one week.

6.title: Cheshire
6.plot: Phil travels to Lach Dennis, in Cheshire, to help a couple who are living life in the dog house.

7.title: Glasgow
7.plot: Phil travels to the Glasgow suburb of Giffnock to try to attract some buyers to a bungalow that's been in the same family for 37 years.

8.title: Ashbourne, Derbyshire
8.plot: Phil helps divorcees Sylvia and Bill sell their semi that's been loitering on the market for over a year. After 54 years of marriage they've decided to separate, sell their home, and move on.

9.title: Colchester
9.plot: Phil meets Duncan and Rhonda, a couple with a young baby who are keen to sell up. But after a month on the market they still haven't had any viewings.

10.title: Northwich, Cheshire
10.plot: Phil helps a couple in Cheshire who have outgrown their home, advising them on how to make it look attractive to buyers at an open viewing in just a week.

11.title: Southend-on-Sea
11.plot: Phil helps serial mover June Seymour. Three months without an offer on her latest pad has stalled June's moving ways.

12.title: Swanscombe, Kent
12.plot: Phil visits Swanscombe in Kent and the childhood home of Chris Fuller.

13.title: Largs, Scotland
13.plot: Phil visits John and Paul Campbell in Largs on Scotland's west coast, hoping to convince the brothers to clean up their act after letting 11 months go by without finding a buyer.

14.title: Glasgow
14.plot: Phil goes undercover to view an outdated property in Uddingston on the outskirts of Glasgow. He meets Pamela and Ian, whose five-bed has only had 12 viewings in six months.

15.title: Sittingbourne, Kent
15.plot: Neil and Jackie Harris in Sittingbourne, Kent, are desperate for more space for them and their two boys. But Phil discovers a house with a spiral stairway hiding mounds of clutter.

16.title: Tunstall, Kent
16.plot: Phil travels to Tunstall in Kent, to the country cottage of Sarah Sewells and Andrew Morris. After three months on the market, is it the botched DIY jobs that are holding the property back?

17.title: Folkestone
17.plot: Phil comes to the rescue of grandmother Elaine Care, whose four bedroom semi in Folkestone has been on the market for a whopping two years.

18.title: Worthing
18.plot: Phil travels to Worthing, on a mission to sell beside the seaside.

19.title: Edinburgh
19.plot: In Edinburgh, Phil meets retiree Patricia Cameron, who is desperate to sell her inherited childhood home in the upmarket Braidhill area of the city.

20.title: Biddulph, Staffordshire
20.plot: In Biddulph, Staffordshire, Phil hopes to help Mark and Denise James find a buyer for their three bed semi.

21.title: Harrogate
21.plot: Phil heads to North Yorkshire, to help Pam to sell a house that's fallen into disrepair and requires some much needed attention.

22.title: Weybridge
22.plot: Phil visits a not so swinging 60s pad in Weybridge. It belongs to brother and sister Nigel and Beverley Mort, who inherited it when their mother passed away.

23.title: Marsden
23.plot: Phil heads to Marsden, West Yorkshire, to help pensioners Malcolm and Muriel bring their house out of the past and into the present day.

24.title: Bolton
24.plot: Secret Agent Phil wants to try to turn around Danny's tatty terrace house, which needs some serious TLC if it's ever going to sell.

25.title: Worthing
25.plot: Phil faces a tough mission helping single mum Zoe to tame her house, which suffers from doggie odour, mess and much clutter.

26.title: Fixby, West Yorkshire
26.plot: Phil helps retiree Jean, who desperately needs help shifting her home near Huddersfield, which has been on the market for 13 months.

27.title: Ashurst Wood, West Sussex
27.plot: Phil heads to Ashurst Wood, West Sussex, to help retirees Tim and Gina turn their dark and cluttered 1950s house into a bang-up-to-date des res.

28.title: Grappnehall, Warrington
28.plot: Phil is in Grappnehall, Warrington, helping Colin Brunold sell his four bed house that's been on the market for five months.

29.title: Rawdon, West Yorkshire
29.plot: Phil meets Alan and Wendy, whose family home of eight years has been on the market without an offer for over 24 months. He finds a split-level house on a slope, with a tricky layout and tired décor.

30.title: Haselmere
30.plot: Phil is in the market town of Haslemere, Surrey, taking on a maisonette that won't sell and an owner that should know better.

31.title: Yeadon, Leeds
31.plot: Phil helps the Seals family who are desperate to sell up and downsize. But with their house bursting with years of clutter, it's a pipe dream unless Phil can convince them to be brutal with the mess.

32.title: Queensbury, Yorkshire
32.plot: Phil goes to Queensbury, Yorkshire, to help retiree Mary. Widowed, and with her children having flown the nest, Mary is desperate to move on, but will she have to drop her current asking price?

33.title: Braunstone Town, Leicester
33.plot: In Braunstone Town, Leicester, Phil must help Pauline and her daughter Rebecca sell their tired and tatty semi.

34.title: Reigate, Surrey
34.plot: Phil helps recently retired couple Lenny and Mary, who want to return to their roots in Ireland.

35.title: The Wirral
35.plot: Phil goes undercover in the picturesque Wirral village of Irby, where he's on a mission to get to grips with Dave and Emma's five bed semi.

36.title: Stamford, Lincolnshire
36.plot: In Stamford, Lincolnshire, Phil tries to help Mark and Tina sell their detached three bed house as they bid to downsize.

37.title: Ashington, West Sussex
37.plot: Phil visits meets the Drakes, who need to sell their house if their retirement plans are to come to fruition. The couple dream of travelling the world in their campervan with beloved dog Zoki.

38.title: Stockton Heath, Warrington
38.plot: Phil travels to the affluent area of Stockton Heath, Warrington, to help Pauline and Alan, whose property has been on the market for three months without any offers.

39.title: Huddersfield
39.plot: Phil travels to Huddersfield to help a home in crisis. David Wadsworth's cottage has got some decidedly dodgy and dated decor, a bare and barren kitchen and a jungle for a garden.

1.title: Waterlooville
1.plot: Purple-loving Pauline has been struggling to sell her three-bed terrace for six months in Waterlooville, near Portsmouth. Phil soon discovers it's not just about the purple, there's asbestos too.

2.title: Melton Mowbray
2.plot: Phil and Aud Briars have been trying to sell their home in Melton Mowbray for six months and Phil Spencer thinks some hard graft and a change of colour scheme will help the couple secure a buyer.

3.title: Gosforth
3.plot: Mother and son Barbara and Paul Bainbridge have been trying to shift their four-bed for more than seven months in Gosforth in Newcastle.

4.title: Edinburgh
4.plot: Jason and Maya Lawie have been trying to sell up for seven months so they can move to Lancashire. They're a creative couple, but could this be exactly what's putting off potential buyers?

5.title: Sittingbourne
5.plot: Phil gives Laura Blogg a Secret Agent surprise. He's positive he can get a deal on the table for her four bedder. But first there's the small matter of seven pets to contend with.

6.title: Winnersh
6.plot: Martin and Yvonne Davies' family home hasn't found a buyer in 18 months. Phil steps in to help and promises with a week's hard graft he can shift it. Nobody will be working harder than daughter Emily.

7.title: Dartford
7.plot: Grandmother Laura Dayachandra is desperate to downsize but despite having dozens of buyers through the door of her three bed in Dartford, she can't seal the deal.

8.title: York
8.plot: Phil tries to sell Steve and Jacqui's bungalow in York which has carp in the garden and carpet on the walls.

9.title: Mid-Calder
9.plot: Phil heads to Mid-Calder. Donald Ferguson is selling up so he and his girlfriend Marie can move into a place they both own, but his semi hasn't shifted in two long years.

10.title: Gravesend
10.plot: In Gravesend, Karen Spellar has been struggling to find a buyer for her three-bed for almost a year. Phil's determined to help so he's stepping in as her Secret Agent and planning a makeover mission.

11.title: St Leonards on Sea
11.plot: Almost a fifth of Brits want to live near the sea, but it seems nobody wants Ken and Tricia Bolton's house in St Leonards on Sea, despite its incredible views of the Channel.

12.title: Newcastle
12.plot: There's plenty for Phil Spencer to tackle in Newcastle when he tries to sell a five-bed house for Graham, Jane and their horse-loving family.

13.title: Thame, Oxfordshire
13.plot: Phil travels to Thame in Oxfordshire where he helps a family sell a house packed with pot plants and penguins.

14.title: Barrow Upon Soar, Leicestershire
14.plot: Phil travels to the Leicestershire village of Barrow Upon Soar, where John Lord is trying to find a buyer. But John's not the only inhabitant - there are animals everywhere, including pet lizards.

15.title: Alexandria, Scotland
15.plot: Liz and Steve Mitchell's four bed near Loch Lomond has been on the market for three years. It doesn't take Phil long to see that Liz's love of colour is blinding buyers.

16.title: Whitley Bay
16.plot: Laura Staines and her partner Gavin want to sell their Whitley Bay three-bedder and buy a bigger house. But it's been more than a year on the market and they still haven't found a buyer.

17.title: Reading
17.plot: In Tilehurst, Reading, Phil meets Dan and his son Chester, who are struggling to sell their very blokey three-bed with a motorbike in the back garden.

18.title: Watford
18.plot: Arancha Burnell's house has been stuck on the market for two years with a whopping 60 viewings. Phil finds dated décor and a bedroom that looks like a Swedish sauna.

19.title: Strood, Kent
19.plot: Phil helps Helen and Paul Merrick turn around the stalled sale of their house after eight months on the market. But will the owners be willing to change their ways?

20.title: Penicuik
20.plot: In Penicuik in Scotland, Phil visits a house that's been stuck on the market for more than three years. Nonetheless he's convinced he can help owner Vivian land a buyer in a week.
